{
    "m_SGVersion": 0,
    "m_Type": "UnityEditor.ShaderGraph.StickyNoteData",
    "m_ObjectId": "6becd21ab44849d5b839df435d5287b7",
    "m_Title": "4. Normal masking",
    "m_Content": "Very similarly, for the normal information we will load the cobblestones_n.png texture in a Sample Texture 2D node, and we will Lerp its RGBA output with a Vector3 = (0, 0, 1). As before, use the output of Step 2 as the interpolant.\n\nFeed the output of Lerp into Fragment > Normal.",
    "m_TextSize": 0,
    "m_Theme": 0,
    "m_Position": {
        "serializedVersion": "2",
        "x": 1458.0,
        "y": -39.33333206176758,
        "width": 358.150390625,
        "height": 155.33328247070313
    },
    "m_Group": {
        "m_Id": ""
    }
}

{
    "m_SGVersion": 0,
    "m_Type": "UnityEditor.Rendering.HighDefinition.ShaderGraph.HDLitData",
    "m_ObjectId": "7071f2770bf44a189bfc3970a391e8a3",
    "m_RayTracing": false,
    "m_MaterialType": 0,
    "m_MaterialTypeMask": 2,
    "m_RefractionModel": 0,
    "m_SSSTransmission": true,
    "m_EnergyConservingSpecular": true,
    "m_ClearCoat": false
}

{
    "m_SGVersion": 0,
    "m_Type": "UnityEditor.ShaderGraph.StickyNoteData",
    "m_ObjectId": "771207c037874dc9ad6ad04379a6de45",
    "m_Title": "2. Computing the mask",
    "m_Content": "Get the B component of the output of Step 1, which corresponds to the H (Height) channel. This contains data in [0; 1]. For now, let's Remap to [-1; 1]. Then, multiply the result by a new float parameter called Saturation, and feed the result of the multiplication through an Hyperbolic Tangent node. This allows us to control how sharp we want our transition between gold and stone to be.\n\nTo complete the mask computation, Negate the output of Hyperbolic Tangent and Remap it to [0; 1].",
    "m_TextSize": 0,
    "m_Theme": 0,
    "m_Position": {
        "serializedVersion": "2",
        "x": -680.6666259765625,
        "y": -412.66668701171877,
        "width": 563.3331298828125,
        "height": 155.3333740234375
    },
